.TH MOR 1 "2026-03-31" "mor 0.7.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mor \- a shared memory store for humans and AI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mor
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ arguments ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mor
stores knowledge as markdown files with YAML frontmatter, indexed by SQLite
FTS5 with optional vector embeddings. It provides a CLI, MCP server, and HTTP
API for managing memories.
.PP
Memories are stored in
.I ~/.config/mor/memories/
(overridable via
.BR MOR_HOME ).
Each memory has an ID (UUID), title, optional description, tags, type, and
markdown content.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Search
.TP
.BI "find " query
Full-text search using FTS5 (tokenized, stemmed).
.RS
.TP
.BI \-l ", " \-\-limit " " n
Max results (default 20).
.TP
.BI \-s ", " \-\-threshold " " n
Minimum relevance score 0\-1 (default 0.3).
.RE
.TP
.BI "grep " pattern
Search memory content by substring or regex.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-n ", " \-\-limit " " n
Max results (default 20).
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-ignore\-case
Case-insensitive matching.
.TP
.BR \-E ", " \-\-regex
Treat pattern as a JavaScript regular expression.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-long
Show file paths.
.RE
.SS Create and Edit
.TP
.BI "add " "[file|url]"
Add a memory from a file, URL, stdin, or \fB$EDITOR\fR. Without arguments,
opens the editor.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-t ", " \-\-title " " title
Memory title.
.TP
.BI \-d ", " \-\-description " " text
Short description.
.TP
.BI \-\-tags " " tags
Comma-separated tags.
.TP
.BI \-\-type " " type
Memory type (see \fBTYPES\fR).
.RE
.TP
.BI "edit " query
Open a memory in \fB$EDITOR\fR.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Edit frontmatter too.
.RE
.TP
.BI "update " query
Update metadata or content of an existing memory.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-t ", " \-\-title " " title
New title.
.TP
.BI \-d ", " \-\-description " " text
New description.
.TP
.BI \-\-tags " " tags
New tags (comma-separated).
.TP
.BI \-\-type " " type
New type.
.TP
.BI \-\-content\-from " " source
Read new content from file or \fB\-\fR for stdin.
.RE
.SS Read and Export
.TP
.BI "cat " query
Print memory content to stdout.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Include YAML frontmatter.
.RE
.TP
.BI "cp " "query dest"
Copy memory content to a file.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Include YAML frontmatter.
.RE
.SS Manage
.TP
.BI "rm " id
Remove a memory by UUID or UUID prefix (8+ characters).
.TP
.B ls
List all memories, sorted by last updated.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-n ", " \-\-limit " " n
Max results.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-long
Show type, date, tags, and file path.
.TP
.B \-\-tags
List all tags with counts.
.TP
.B \-\-types
List all types with counts.
.RE
.TP
.B sync
Pull remote changes via git, commit and push local changes.
.TP
.B reindex
Rebuild the search index from memory files.
.TP
.BI "import " dir
Import \fI.md\fR files from a directory.
.SS Server
.TP
.B mcp
Start an MCP server over stdio. Used by AI assistants.
.TP
.B serve
Start an HTTP server for remote access.
.RS
.TP
.BI \-p ", " \-\-port " " port
Listen port (default 7677).
.TP
.BI \-H ", " \-\-host " " host
Listen host (default 127.0.0.1).
.TP
.BI \-\-token " " token
Require Bearer token authentication.
.TP
.B \-\-mcp
Enable MCP endpoint at \fI/mcp\fR.
.RE
.TP
.B version
Show version information.
.SH FILTER OPTIONS
The following options are available for
.BR find ,
.BR grep ,
and
.BR ls :
.TP
.BI \-\-type " " type
Filter by memory type (comma-separated, glob patterns).
.TP
.BI \-\-tag " " pattern
Filter by tag (glob pattern).
.TP
.BI \-\-repo " " pattern
Filter by repository (glob pattern).
.TP
.BI \-\-ext " " ext
Filter by file extension.
.SH TYPES
.TP
.B knowledge
General knowledge (default).
.TP
.B snippet
Code snippet.
.TP
.B file
Saved file.
.TP
.B user
User preferences and profile.
.TP
.B feedback
Workflow feedback and corrections.
.TP
.B project
Project context and decisions.
.TP
.B reference
Pointers to external resources.
.SH QUERY RESOLUTION
When a command accepts a
.IR query ,
it is resolved in order: full UUID, UUID prefix (8+ characters), filename,
then full-text search.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MOR_HOME
Override the configuration directory (default \fI~/.config/mor\fR).
.TP
.B EDITOR
Editor used by
.B add
and
.BR edit .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/mor/config.json
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/mor/memories/
Memory storage directory.
.TP
.I ~/.config/mor/index.db
SQLite search index.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file supports:
.TP
.B memoryDir
Path to memory storage directory.
.TP
.B dbPath
Path to SQLite database.
.TP
.B autosync
Automatically git sync after add, update, and remove (boolean).
.TP
.B embedding
Embedding provider configuration (openai, azure-openai, ollama, none).
.TP
.B server
Remote server connection (url, token).
.TP
.B serve
HTTP server defaults (port, host, token, mcp).
.SH EXAMPLES
Add a memory from a file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor add src/utils.ts
.fi
.RE
.PP
Search for memories:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor find "authentication flow"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Grep for an exact string:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor grep "createServer" \-i
.fi
.RE
.PP
Grep with a regex:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor grep \-E "async\\s+function" \-i
.fi
.RE
.PP
List memories tagged with "config":
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor ls \-\-tag config
.fi
.RE
.PP
Update tags on a memory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor update 8da8d8f2 \-\-tags "go,concurrency"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start the HTTP server with auth and MCP:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mor serve \-\-token secret \-\-mcp
.fi
.RE
